@LaPetiteSoeurDeLouis You could be in for a rough ride with OpenAI gym.
https://github.com/deeplearning4j/rl4j/issues/59

Not really DL4J s fault as OpenAI itself looks a bit unstable.

@polisettyManoj complex number support in ND4J isn't functional at present, sorry
there's just not enough demand relative to other (higher priority) features for us to get to it yet
though eventually, yes - it's something we will support in the future

@amcelroy 
> Is there a way to have the EarlyStoppingTrainer stop based on F1?

yes - use this score calculator: https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/blob/master/deeplearning4j-nn/src/main/java/org/deeplearning4j/earlystopping/scorecalc/ClassificationScoreCalculator.java#L17

@StefanoSamele
> it seems that for feedForward inputType the batchdim seems to be in position 0 and for convolutional InputType, the batchdim is in postion 3

No, but the InputType.convolutional args order is different to activations shape order

@lemair you're doing some sort of a count operation / reduction there
so long is expected
can't say much more without seeing code

@ansarisam please use !gist in the future for large code
and no, there's no issue with SharedTrainingMaster, though it does have an extra hyperparameter to tune, namely the gradient threshold
check the "distributed deep learning" pages here for an explanation on that - http://deeplearning4j.org/docs/latest/

@ansarisam 
> When running convolution network training, I am getting the following error.

you are probably mixing scala versions? (also, again, use gist in the future)

@ansarisam a poorly chosen gradient threshold (you're setting it in your config) can break training, unfortunately
something like 1e-3 isn't a bad start, but you can try 10x and 100x smaller or larger too
the initial threshold doesn't have to be perfect, but if it's very wrong it can not work

